  "text": "TLR4 plays a key role in the development of innate defence mechanisms and adaptive immunity against pathogens, and Myd88 acts as an intermediate linker for inflammatory motility [CITATION_1] . Compared to the control group ( Figure 5A ), LPS stimulation significantly upregulated TLR4 and Myd88 protein expression, indicating that LPS induced TLR4 and Myd88 activation. However, betaine treatment effectively inhibited TLR4 and Myd88 protein expression in N9 microglial cells. Given that Myd88 signalling mediates the NF-\u03baB pathway, we evaluated the activation of the NF-\u03baB pathway by western blot analysis. As shown in Figure 5B -D, LPS stimulation resulted in the phosphorylation of I\u03baB kinase (IKK-\u03b2), I\u03baB-\u03b1, and NF-\u03baB p65 but did not affecting IKK-\u03b2, I\u03baB-\u03b1 and NF-\u03baBp-65 their activity expression. However, betaine treatment decreased the expression of p-IKK-\u03b2, p-I\u03baB-\u03b1, and p-NF-\u03baB p65. These results indicated that betaine inhibited the LPS-induced activation of the TLR4/NF-\u03baB pathways in N9 microglial cells in vitro. MIDO was used as a positive control. (B-D) Determination of IKK-\u03b2, P-IKK-\u03b2, I\u03ba\u0392-\u03b1, P-I\u03ba\u0392-\u03b1, NF-\u03ba\u0392, and p-NF-\u03ba\u0392 protein levels by western blot analysis. MIDO was used as a positive control. Data are presented as the means \u00b1 SEM of three independent experiments. The control group included untreated cells. Untreated cells served as a control group. # p < 0.05, compared to the control group; * p < 0.05 and ** p < 0.01, compared to the LPS-treated group.",
